text: 149 is a natural number. It comes after 148 and before 150. == Properties == *149 is a prime number. That means it can only be divided evenly by 1 and itself. *It is the 35th prime number. *When you reverse the digits of 149, you get 941, which is also a prime number. A prime that stays prime when its digits are reversed is called an emirp. Category:Integers
title: 149 (number)
